    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>This recipe takes around 5-10 min to prep, so get your casserole dish and all your ingredients ready, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Make sure your dish is oven-proof and safe to use on the hob. Don't have one? Start cooking in a large, wide-based pan then transfer to an oven-proof dish and cover tightly with foil</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chipotle-mexican-style-chicken-stew-with-buttered-corn-and-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7, and take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based <strong>hob-safe</strong> <strong>oven-proof casserole dish</strong> with a matching lid with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>chicken </strong>and cook for 3-4 min on each side</p><p>(Doubled your protein? Use 2 pans!)</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chipotle-mexican-style-chicken-stew-with-buttered-corn-and-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a kettle, then peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Once the chicken is lightly browned, add your <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong> and <strong>ground coriander</strong> with your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong>,<strong> chopped garlic </strong>and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong>, then give it a good mix up and cook for 30 secs</p><p>Add your <strong>tomato paste</strong> and <strong>chipotle paste </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)<strong> </strong>with a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chipotle-mexican-style-chicken-stew-with-buttered-corn-and-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add 350ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[450ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [600ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>and<strong> </strong>bring to the boil</p><p>Once boiling, cover with a lid and put the dish in the oven for 30-35 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) and the sauce has thickened \u2013 this is your <strong>chicken stew</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chipotle-mexican-style-chicken-stew-with-buttered-corn-and-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, reboil a kettle</p><p>Add your <strong>white long grain rice </strong>to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong> with 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]<strong> </strong></span><strong>boiled water</strong>, then cover tightly with <strong>tin foil</strong> and put the dish on a baking tray</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chipotle-mexican-style-chicken-stew-with-buttered-corn-and-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>sweetcorn cobettes</strong> to a large piece of <strong>tin foil </strong>with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and a knob of <strong>butter</strong>, then scrunch the <strong>tin foil </strong>around the corn until tightly sealed and add to the other side of the baking tray</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 25-30 min or until the corn is tender and the rice is cooked \u2013 this is your <strong>baked rice</strong> and <strong>buttered corn</strong></p><p>Use this time to clear up, set the table, have a cup of tea or simply chill!</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chipotle-mexican-style-chicken-stew-with-buttered-corn-and-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken stew is ready, remove the dish from the oven</p><p>Roll your <strong>lime[s]</strong> with your hand on a hard surface (to release more juice) and cut in half, then add a generous squeeze of <strong>lime juice</strong> to the stew and give it a good mix up</p><p>Set aside for 2-3 min for the flavours to develop \u2013 this is your <strong>chipotle</strong> <strong>Mexican-style chicken stew</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chipotle-mexican-style-chicken-stew-with-buttered-corn-and-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>chipotle Mexican-style chicken stew </strong>with the <strong>baked rice </strong>and<strong> buttered corn </strong>to the side</p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining lime</strong> into 1 wedge per person and garnish with a <strong>lime wedge</strong></p><p>Dig in!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
